Name: Form 87 - QA Form
Details
Details
Work Order Number:
Product Description:
Date of Manufacture:
Preliminary Activities
1 - Review Work Instruction
Specification/Control Documents - Scope of works, Customer order, Client supplied drawings, Precast shop drawings, Lifting design drawings
2 - Certification of lifting points/ cast in items
Specification/Control Documents - AS/NZS 4671, AS 3679, AS 3850, AS 4680
Acceptance Criteria - All materials to be new and free of defects. All materials to have manufacturer/supplier test certificates supplied.
Verifying Documents - Lifting Drawing certified by Ancon
3 - Concrete mix design
Specification/Control Documents - AS 3600
Acceptance Criteria - Concrete Mix design meets requirement S50 MRWA Mix (MJBMRWAS50) as approved.
Verifying Documents - Mix design, Historical records
4 - Pre-Inspection Meeting
Acceptance Criteria - To promote and coordinate effort by Contractor and Vendor
Materials
5 - Assemble reinforcing cage
Specification/Control Documents - MJB Production Drawing
Acceptance Criteria - Drawings are available, bars placed as shown on MJB Production Drawing.
Pre-Pour
6 - Set up formwork/moulds
Specification/Control Documents - AS 1597, AS 3610
Acceptance Criteria - Formwork is suitable for surface finish. Dimensions checked in accordance with MJB production drawings. Refer Table 2.7 Dimension Tolerances.
7 - Apply form release
Specification/Control Documents - AS 1597, AS 3600, AS 3850
Acceptance Criteria - Applied prior to pouring
8 - Installation of reinforcing
Specification/Control Documents - AS 1597, AS 3600, AS 3850
Acceptance Criteria - Cover and location of reinforcement checked.
9 - Installation of cast-in items (Lifting Pins, Ferrules etc)
Specification/Control Documents - AS 1597, AS 3600, AS 3850
Acceptance Criteria - Cover and location of cast-in items checked.
Batching Concrete
10 - Concrete testing
Specification/Control Documents - AS 1379, AS 1012
Acceptance Criteria - Compressive strength test. Minimum 28 day compressive strength for S50 is 58 Mpa. Testing required every 20m3. Slump Testing. Slump = 160mm ±40mm
Verifying Documents - Concrete Test Report
Concrete Placement, Handling & Finishing
11 - Pour concrete
Specification/Control Documents - AS 3600
Acceptance Criteria - Correct concrete supplied. Concrete temperature between 10-32 degrees Celsius at discharge. Freefall distance less than 2m.
Verifying Documents - Concrete delivery docket
12 - Finishing
Specification/Control Documents - AS 1597, AS 3600, AS 3610
Acceptance Criteria - Finish level to be trowelled as per AS 3610
Post Pour
13 - Remove from mould
Specification/Control Documents - AS 1597, AS 3600
Acceptance Criteria - Dimensions, lifting points and visual appearance are correct and within tolerance. Minimum of 20MPa or 3 days, whichever is earlier.
14 - Curing
Specification/Control Documents - AS 3799
Acceptance Criteria - All precast concrete cured by Master Builders Solutions Masterkure CC 100WB
Repairs (if required) and storage of product
15 - Identify and repair defects
Specification/Control Documents - AS 3610, AS 1597
Acceptance Criteria - Identify defects, complete repairs as directed by MJB work instructions.
16 - Final inspection and storage of items
Specification/Control Documents - Australian Standards
Acceptance Criteria - All items inspected, approved product have quality tick, moved to storage area prior to despatch.
17 - Quality Documentation
Acceptance Criteria - MJB quality documentation to be forwarded to customer
Load Check

Confirm that products are not damaged and up to MJB standards
If Pipes are on the load, ensure rubber rings are also loaded and take photos
Load has been strapped and secured
Photos to be taken of each product, strapping and a wide view photo of the truck/trailers
Once all checks complete sign off loading docket, attach a photo and return to driver
